ALFRANK v. MINNESOTA DOCK CO. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. June 11, 1902.) No. 1,067. In Error to the Circuit Court of the United States-for the Northern District of Ohio. J. H. McGiffert, for plaintiff in error. Ford, Snyder, Henry & McGraw, for defendant in error.

Before LURTON, DAY, and SEYERENS, Circuit Judges.

No opinion. Affirmed, with costs, by consent of the parties.
